cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques for multilingual weakly supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new method for encoding expectations as constraints and training a discriminative CRF model using Generalized Expectation Criteria, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques for NLP tasks, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
